Class InvalidInputFileTest

  • public class InvalidInputFileTest
extends RecommendationSubtest
    Starts the program with several invalid input files without performing any actions. Checks if the program outputs error messages.

    1.1

      • basicCircleTest

        public void basicCircleTest()
        Asserts that the tested class detects and prints an error message for input files that form circles in the constructed graph. This method tests with short input files but covers different syntactical constructs, including lines relating shop elements with themselves.

      • caseSensitivityTest

        public void caseSensitivityTest()
        Asserts that the tested class checks for the right case in the input file.

      • circleTest

        public void circleTest()
        Asserts that the tested class detetects and prints an error message for input files that form circles in the constructed graph. This method tests with a longer input file and all relations.

      • emptyLinesTest

        public void emptyLinesTest()
        Asserts that the tested class prints an error message for empty lines, which are syntactical errors.
